%20having%20much%20of%20a%20plan%2C%20we%20found%20family%20and%20had%20an%20incredible%20trip.%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Towns%20Swantkoski%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EWe%20traveled%20to%20South%20Korea%20with%20my%20husband's%20grandmother%20in%20hopes%20of%20finding%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flong-lost-twins-sold-off-at-birth-reunite-via-tiktok-2024-1%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elong-lost%20family%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOur%20only%20plan%20was%20to%20visit%20her%20hometown%20with%20the%20names%20and%20ages%20of%20the%20family%20she%20remembered.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDespite%20little%20research%2C%20we%20found%20five%20of%20her%20siblings%20and%20other%20family%20members.%20It%20was%20amazing.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20last%2015%20years%2C%20my%20husband's%20family%20has%20immersed%20me%20in%20South%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkorean-culture-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EKorean%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20mostly%20by%20way%20of%20my%20stomach.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhenever%20his%20grandmother%2C%20Kim%2C%20visited%2C%20she'd%20fill%20our%20kitchen%20with%20the%20delicious%20aromas%20of%20dishes%20she%20grew%20up%20with%2C%20from%20japchae%20to%20mandu.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20she'd%20share%20memories%20from%20her%20time%20in%20South%20Korea%20before%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoved-from-venezuela-to-vermont-making-friends-hard-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eimmigrated%20to%20the%20US%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%2050%20years%20ago.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20always%20a%20tender%20conversation%20topic%2C%20one%20that%20reminded%20her%20of%20a%20life%20and%20family%20left%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe'd%20lost%20touch%20with%20her%20relatives%20there%20and%20hadn't%20been%20back%20to%20visit.%20For%20years%2C%20traveling%20to%20a%20place%20she%20once%20called%20%26quot%3Bhome%26quot%3B%20was%20never%20a%20topic%20of%20much%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20Kim%20reached%20her%20mid-70s%2C%20she%20realized%20she'd%20rather%20try%20to%20reconnect%20with%20her%20family%20than%20have%20unanswered%20questions%20about%20their%20lives%20and%20what%20had%20happened%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20support%20and%20encouragement%20of%20her%20children%20and%20grandchildren%2C%20we%20began%20planning%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftips-travel-south-korea-seoul-mistakes-tourists-make-guide-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etrip%20to%20South%20Korea%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228bf8ca3d-9484-4a7f-b470-267ab10aac2d%5C%22%3EDespite%20the%20hurdles%20ahead%2C%20we%20traveled%20to%20South%20Korea%20with%20hope%20and%20anticipation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Author%20Alyssa%20Towns%20Swantkoski%20with%20grandmother%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68711ac0f748d8c055f570df%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWe%20headed%20to%20South%20Korea%20for%20what%20we%20hoped%20would%20be%20the%20trip%20of%20a%20lifetime.%20%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Towns%20Swantkoski%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20summer%2C%20a%20group%20of%2013%20of%20us%20packed%20our%20bags%20and%20flew%20from%20the%20US%20to%20Seoul.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKim%20preferred%20not%20to%20do%20any%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fancestrydna-genetic-test-review-ancestry-update-2019-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eancestral%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20the%20trip.%20So%2C%20after%20a%20few%20days%20in%20Seoul%2C%20we'd%20travel%20to%20her%20hometown%20village%20of%20Eungwon-ri%20in%20Cheonan%20with%20a%20piece%20of%20paper%20with%20relatives'%20names%20and%20their%20approximate%20ages..%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20plan%20to%20locate%20her%20family%20was%20vague%20and%20optimistic%20at%20best%2C%20and%20we%20recognized%20that%20the%20language%20barrier%20would%20be%20one%20of%20our%20most%20significant%20hurdles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20we%20stayed%20hopeful.%20When%20we%20arrived%20in%20Eungwon-ri%2C%20we%20checked%20into%20a%20small%20hotel%20near%20where%20Kim%20grew%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20first%20asked%20the%20hotel%20staff%20if%20they%20recognized%20the%20names%20on%20the%20list.%20They%20didn't%2C%20but%20they%20eagerly%20offered%20to%20ask%20around%20and%20spread%20the%20word%20of%20our%20arrival.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20we%20tried%20the%20caf%C3%A9%20located%20up%20the%20street%20from%20the%20hotel%2C%20but%20to%20no%20avail.%20However%2C%20much%20like%20in%20any%20small%20town%2C%20news%20of%20our%20arrival%20and%20the%20names%20of%20those%20we%20were%20searching%20for%20quickly%20spread%20throughout%20Eungwon-ri.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20about%20an%20hour%2C%20a%20woman%20in%20a%20restaurant%20nearby%20caught%20wind%20of%20our%20search%20and%20invited%20us%20to%20join%20her%20inside%20as%20she%20called%20around%20town.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChatter%20filled%20the%20room%20as%20she%20carried%20on%20conversations%20in%20her%20native%20tongue%2C%20of%20which%20we%20had%20little%20understanding.%20With%20the%20help%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-china-translate-travel-app-english-tourist-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etranslation%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20contextual%20cues%2C%20the%20woman%20told%20Kim%20that%20her%20brother%20was%20on%20the%20way%20to%20see%20us%20and%20would%20arrive%20in%20half%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThirty%20minutes%20never%20pass%20more%20slowly%20than%20when%20it's%20about%20to%20change%20your%20life.%20As%20a%20car%20pulled%20up%20outside%20the%20restaurant%20and%20a%20man%20stepped%20out%2C%20we%20eagerly%20stormed%20the%20parking%20lot.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20and%20Kim%20shared%20their%20parents'%20names%20and%20some%20other%20details%20for%20additional%20confirmation%2C%20and%20we%20soon%20got%20the%20news%20we'd%20been%20hoping%20for%3A%20We'd%20done%20it.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20the%20kindness%20of%20the%20people%20of%20Eungwon-ri%2C%20my%20husband's%20grandmother%20was%20reunited%20with%20her%20brother%20in%20less%20than%20three%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224031fcae-0a28-4e5e-bee4-c85bf8f142be%5C%22%3EOur%20family%20has%20grown%20significantly%20because%20of%20this%20once-in-a-lifetime%20trip%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Group%20of%20people%20smiling%20in%20South%20Korea%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68628e3ff748d8c055f49ff8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWe%20loved%20seeing%20South%20Korea%20with%20family.%20%3Cp%3EAlyssa%20Towns%20Swantkoski%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20evening%2C%20we%20had%20dinner%20together%20right%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20Eungwon-ri.%20Her%20brother%20began%20notifying%20other%20family%20members%20of%20our%20surprise%20arrival.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20hours%20and%20days%20that%20followed%2C%20Kim%20reconnected%20with%20five%20of%20her%20siblings%2C%20as%20well%20as%20some%20of%20her%20nieces%20and%20nephews.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20despite%20over%2050%20years%20of%20separation%20and%20most%20of%20us%20having%20never%20met%2C%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdna-test-helps-reunite-long-lost-siblings-after-34-years-2018-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elong-lost%20relatives%3C%2Fa%3E%20took%20us%20in%20and%20welcomed%20us%20into%20their%20lives%20and%20homes%20with%20open%20arms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Group%20of%20people%20smiling%20together%20in%20South%20Korea%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68628ebd85e81483682d06e0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%