%20what%20they%20care%20about%20and%20what%20they%20want%20to%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20Lambros%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20having%20candidates%20ask%20questions%20from%20the%20start%20tends%20to%20elicit%20%26quot%3Bdeeper%20and%20richer%20answers%26quot%3B%20in%20general.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ce06abc0-5b11-4a4b-b583-ecb006ff3061%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20LLM%20'can't%20feign%20interest'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20candidates%20start%20with%20their%20questions%20could%20force%20some%20job%20seekers%20to%20avoid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-debates-over-use-ai-chatbots-tech-job-interviews-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erelying%20on%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20them%20skate%20through%20interviews.%20And%20any%20measures%20that%20lead%20to%20a%20more%20%26quot%3Bfree-form%20discussion%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20candidates%20can%20dig%20into%20what%20they%20want%20to%20know%2C%20can%20highlight%20when%20people%20aren't%20well%20prepared%20or%20engaged%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20large%20language%20model%20%26quot%3Bcan't%20feign%20interest%2C%26quot%3B%20Lambros%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EElizabeth%20Lotardo%2C%20a%20leadership%20consultant%20who%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BLeading%20Yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20told%20BI%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frecruiters-favorite-job-interview-questions-how-to-answer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Easking%20the%20interview%20subject%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20go%20first%20with%20questions%20is%20likely%20especially%20helpful%20for%20roles%20involving%20leadership%20or%20in%20areas%20like%20sales%20where%20employees%20might%20have%20to%20initiate%20conversations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20approach%20might%20not%20be%20as%20fruitful%20with%20roles%20that%20are%20more%20focused%20on%20completing%20certain%20tasks%20or%20that%20rely%20less%20on%20interpersonal%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELotardo%20sa