5%20million%20in%20funding%20to%20fuel%20expansion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20it%20works%3A%20A%20client%20submits%20a%20brief%20description%20of%20their%20legal%20issue%20on%20OpenLaw's%20site.%20The%20company's%20algorithms%20sift%20through%20its%20database%20of%20pre-screened%20attorneys%20and%20surface%20those%20with%20the%20most%20relevant%20experience.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenLaw%20shares%20case%20details%20with%20those%20lawyers%20who%20respond%20with%20proposals.%20Then%2C%20the%20client%20can%20compare%20options%20and%20pick%20one.%20The%20lawyer%20sends%20over%20a%20contract%2C%20and%20the%20client%20signs%20%E2%80%94%20all%20without%20leaving%20OpenLaw's%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20industry%20is%20dominated%20by%20small%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thomsonreuters.com%2Fen-us%2Fposts%2Flegal%2Fus-small-law-firms-report-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esolo%20practices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20leaving%20most%20lawyers%20to%20juggle%20actual%20legal%20work%20with%20the%20grind%20of%20running%20a%20business.%20OpenLaw%20pitches%20itself%20as%20a%20fix%3A%20by%20connecting%20lawyers%20directly%20with%20clients%2C%20the%20platform%20could%20cut%20down%20on%20marketing%20costs%20and%20free%20up%20time%20for%20the%20stuff%20they%20actually%20went%20to%20law%20school%20to%20do.%20That's%20the%20idea%2C%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuzman%20says%20OpenLaw%20has%20onboarded%20more%20than%20130%20lawyers%20across%20Florida%20and%20Texas%2C%20with%20another%20300%20on%20a%20waitlist.%20So%20far%2C%20the%20platform%20is%20geared%20toward%20high-volume%20practice%20areas%20like%20civil%20litigation%2C%20family%20law%2C%20and%20criminal%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20are%20buying%20in.%20OpenLaw's%20seed%20round%20was%20led%20by%20Flint%20Capital%20and%20Slauson%20%26amp%3B%20Co.%2C%20with%20participation%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flegal-tech-investments-thriving-insights-from-vc-investors-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EZach%20Posner's%3C%2Fa%3E%20The%20LegalTech%20Fund%2C%20Mindful%20Venture%20Capital%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjenny-fielding-techstars-vc-top-female-seed-investor-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJenny%20Fielding's%3C%2Fa%3E%20Everywhere%20Ventures%2C%20Gaingels%2C%20and%20others.%20The%20valuation%20was%20undisclosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuzman%20says%20the%20fresh%20funding%20will%20be%20used%20to%20gas%20up%20new%20markets%2C%20including%20New%20York%2C%20California%2C%20and%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3BUber%20for%20legal%20services%26quot%3B%20pitch%20is%20nothing%20new%2C%20and%20it's%20a%20category%20that's%20seen%20more%20flameouts%20than%20follow-through.%20UpCounsel%2C%20a%20marketplace%20for%20business%20lawyers%2C%20was%20once%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftechcrunch.com%2F2015%2F07%2F28%2F10-million-for-upcounsel-means-small-businesses-can-hire-biglaw-attorneys%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVC-backed%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20buzzy.%20But%20after%20getting%20hit%20with%20a%20flurry%20of%20lawsuits%20and%20struggling%20to%20scale%2C%20it%20announced%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.crunchbase.com%2Fventure%2Fupcounsel-avoids-shutdown-after-last-minute-acquisition-by-enduring-ventures%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplans%20to%20shut%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202020%2C%20only%20to%20be%20rescued%20by%20a%20holding%20company.%20Another%20player%2C%20ContractsCounsel%2C%20has%20been%20around%20for%20years%20with%20a%20similar%20model%2C%20but%20remains%20relatively%20small%20and%20under-the-radar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20actually%20new%20here%3F%20Guzman%20thinks%20it's%20two%20things.%20The%20platform%20aims%20to%20help%20people%20facing%20%26quot%3Breal-life%26quot%3B%20legal%20issues.%20You're%20getting%20divorced.%20Your%20credit%20card%20company%20is%20suing%20you%20to%20collect%20a%20debt.%20The%20other%20marketplaces%2C%20Guzman%20says%2C%20focus%20more%20on%20business%20transactions%20like%20incorporating%20a%20company%20or%20filing%20a%20trademark%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20OpenLaw%20is%20betting%20that%20its%20use%20of%20AI%20will%20give%20it%20an%20edge.%20Guzman%20says%20the%20company%20trawls%20public%20data%20to%20identify%20people%20who%20are%20being%20sued%20%E2%80%94%20often%20before%20those%20individuals%20even%20realize%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20very%20innovative%20early%20warning%20system%20where%20we%20let%20people%20know%20that%20they%20are%20being%20sued%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20them%20to%20know%20that%20they%20have%20options.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20page%20of%20the%20company's%20online%20intake%20form%20asks%2C%20%26quot%3BDid%20you%20receive%20a%20notice%20from%20us%3F%26quot%3B%20Guzman%20declined%20to%20explain%20exactly%20how%20the%20system%20works%2C%20saying%20he%20didn't%20want%20to%20tip%20off%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhether%20OpenLaw's%20model%20proves%20durable%20remains%20an%20open%20question.%20But%20if%20the%20platform%20can%20deliver%20for%20lawyers%20and%20clients%2C%20it%20might%20just%20earn%20a%20place%20beyond%20the%20Google%20search%20bar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20the%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amrussell%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Emrussell%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20%40MeliaRussell.01.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20here's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227995%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Slide%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687928a985e81483682e3533%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOpenLaw's%20mission%20is%20to%20r